    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> [350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>– this is your<strong> herby stock</strong></p><p>Trim the end[s] of your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> keeping the stalk[s] intact</p><p>Without cutting through the stalk[s], carefully slice the<strong> trimmed courgette[s]</strong> into thin strips, lengthways (at approx. 5mm intervals)</p><p>Then, peel lengths of the<strong> sliced courgette[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>until you have a pile of 'courgetti'</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
