    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roughly break your<strong> linguine</strong> up into thirds, add it to the pan along with the <strong>courgetti</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>tomato & basil sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato & basil sauce</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish </strong>with<strong> </strong>200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and press down on the broken linguine so that it's submerged in the sauce</p><p>Place the <strong>browned</strong> <strong>meatballs</strong> on top and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>courgetti & beef meatball bake</strong></p>",
